### Change 2: Backend - DataFormsController.cs (Lines 1290-1310)

**Location**: `MaterialControlCenter/Controllers/DataFormsController.cs`  
**Method**: `GetApprovalChain()` → Manager resolution (role_id 5)

**Before**:
```csharp
if (roleName.Contains("manager") && !roleName.Contains("material"))
{
    // Manager langsung initiator
    var mgr = supChain.ElementAtOrDefault(1);
    if (mgr != null) { resolvedKpks.Add(mgr.Kpk); resolvedNames.Add(mgr.Name ?? mgr.Kpk); }
}
```

**After**:
```csharp
if (roleName.Contains("manager") && !roleName.Contains("material"))
{
    // ── FIX: Manager adalah Supervisor dari Supervisor ──
    // initiatorKpk sekarang adalah supervisor KPK yang dipilih user
    // Cari supervisor dari supervisor ini
    var supervisorEmployee = supChain.ElementAtOrDefault(0);  // Index 0 = supervisor itu sendiri
    if (supervisorEmployee != null && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(supervisorEmployee.Supervisor))
    {
        // Cari supervisor dari supervisor tersebut
        var managerEmployee = dbSSO.GetUserByKpkSSO(supervisorEmployee.Supervisor);
        if (managerEmployee != null)
        {
            resolvedKpks.Add(managerEmployee.Kpk);
            resolvedNames.Add(managerEmployee.Name ?? managerEmployee.Kpk);
            Debug.Print($"[GetApprovalChain] Step 1 Manager (Supervisor's Supervisor): " +
                $"SupervisorKpk={supervisorEmployee.Kpk}, ManagerKpk={managerEmployee.Kpk}");
        }
    }
}
```

**Key Changes**:
- Receives `initiatorKpk` as **Supervisor KPK** (not initiator KPK)
- `supChain[0]` = Supervisor (the one selected by user)
- Looks up `supervisorEmployee.Supervisor` in SSO database
- That supervisor's supervisor becomes the Manager
- Added detailed debug logging for troubleshooting

